(Gains) and Charges” table below.
Excluding the impact of special (gains) and charges and the impacts of the Purolite transaction, our 2021 adjusted
gross margin was 40.9% compared against a 2020 adjusted gross margin of 41.8%. The decrease primarily reflected
increased pricing and higher volumes which were more than offset by significantly higher delivered product costs and
supply constraints, including the impact of the Texas Freeze and Hurricane Ida.
Excluding the impact of special (gains) and charges, our adjusted gross margin was 41.8% and 44.2% for 2020 and
2019, respectively. The decrease primarily reflected the impact of lower volume, reduced operating leverage and
unfavorable business mix, which more than offset pricing.
