commercial paper program and a $2.0 billion Euro commercial paper program. The maximum aggregate amount of
commercial paper that may be issued by the Company under its commercial paper programs may not exceed $2.0
billion.
The Company had $400 million outstanding commercial paper under its U.S. program as of December 31, 2021 and
no outstanding commercial paper under its Euro or U.S. program as of December 31, 2020.
As of December 31, 2021, the Company’s short-term borrowing program was rated A-2 by Standard & Poor’s, P-2 by
Moody’s and F-1 by Fitch.
